
Write a solution to swap the seat id of every two consecutive students. If the number of students is odd, the id of the last student is not swapped.

Return the result table ordered by id in ascending order.

The result format is in the following example.

Example 1:
Input: 
Seat table:
+----+---------+
| id | student |
+----+---------+
| 1  | Abbot   |
| 2  | Doris   |
| 3  | Emerson |
| 4  | Green   |
| 5  | Jeames  |
+----+---------+
Output: 
+----+---------+
| id | student |
+----+---------+
| 1  | Doris   |
| 2  | Abbot   |
| 3  | Green   |
| 4  | Emerson |
| 5  | Jeames  |
+----+---------+
Explanation: 
Note that if the number of students is odd, there is no need to change the last one's seat.

intutition
if the id is odd then increase the +1 thrn it will become even so internally the id changes then at last order by use and it will give u the reusultant result.

sql:

select 
case
when id= (select max(id) from seat) and id% 2=1 then id ## if last odd then retain
when id % 2 =1 then id+1 
else id-1 
end
as id,
student
from Seat
order by id

